{
  "texts": [
    "Various choices are used in practice for the secret key distribution.",
    "Below we list some examples.",
    "• The coefficients of the secret polynomial s are chosen uniformly at random from Z q: this is known as uniform secret.",
    "• The secret polynomial s is chosen according to the error distribution χ e: this is known as normal form secret or Gaussian secret.",
    "• The coefficients of the secret polynomial s are chosen uniformly at random from {-1, 0, 1}: this is known as uniform ternary secret."
  ]
}